Text: For years, Charlotte served with integrity & professionalism as a policy advisor on my team. I have deep respect for her & I am proud of her extraordinary strength & courage. Her story is alarming. Racism, misogyny & harassment have no place anywhere. https://t.co/9qhJzoskAd

Voters in New Jersey made their voices heard, and thanks to the work of @PhilMurphyNJ, state lawmakers, and advocates—marijuana is now legal in New Jersey.

The war on drugs has been a war on people. The road to equity and justice is long, but this is an important first step.

In less than a year we have lost 500,000 of our countrymen and women. This is an unimaginable loss.

As the human toll grows we must hold onto one another—the only way out of this is together.

John Lewis is no longer with us, but today, on what would have been his 81st birthday, I hope we all take a moment to remember him. To remember his humanity, his grace & his love for others. What happened in our country will be talked about for generations to come. If we ignore this, if we excuse it, if we do nothing, we invite this horror back on our country again. This is a moral moment when we need profiles in courage.

History will judge whether we show courage & hold accountable the person who is responsible. Because we all know but for Donald Trump—but for his actions over the weeks leading up to the assault on our Capitol & again during the actual siege—this would not have happened.

Thank you @NickKristof for this urgently necessary column.

“You are growing into consciousness, and my wish for you is that you feel no need to constrict yourself to make other people comfortable.” Ta-Nehisi Coates #BlackHistoryMonth

“We've got to face the fact that some people say you fight fire best with fire, but we say you put fire out best with water. We say you don't fight racism with racism. We're gonna fight racism with solidarity.” Fred Hampton #BlackHistoryMonth

She does not know
her beauty,
she thinks her brown body
has no glory.

If she could dance
naked
under palm trees
and see her image in the river,
she would know.

But there are no palm trees
on the street,
and dish water gives back
no images.

William Waring Cuney, No Images #BHM

With its back against the wall… 
To save the dream for one

I celebrate our ancestors; I celebrate our history; and as we kick off #BlackHistoryMonth, I am driven to write our own story that moves our country toward justice and equality for all. #BHM

Mitch McConnell is no longer Senate Majority Leader.

I am so glad to have @ReverendWarnock, @AlexPadilla4CA & @Ossoff as my newest colleagues.

Now we unite around our new President, stand with him, and pray for his success. https://t.co/zUPBShN7sa

I can feel our ancestors rejoicing today.

A Black and South Asian woman who has blazed trails and shattered glass ceilings is taking the oath of office to become Vice President of the United States.

This is such a proud moment for our country.

We love you, @KamalaHarris. https://t.co/C2mDpwBXPs

Donald Trump is the first president in American history to have been impeached twice.

He has brought shame to his office and this nation.

The Senate must now vote to convict him.

Donald Trump is a threat to our national security and betrayed his oath of office.

The Vice President has failed to take action and invoke the 25th Amendment.

Now we must move forward in Congress with impeachment and remove the threat posed by this president.

Tona’s tireless work in my office on racial justice and criminal justice reform has impacted millions of Americans and generations unborn. I’m so excited to see her continue to serve her country in the Biden Administration. Thank you, Tona. Congrats! https://t.co/mtnj9WrVR9
In the face of darkness, @GabbyGiffords is a true lightworker. Her resilience and determination is a source of strength for our nation during these challenging times. https://t.co/Xv6g2hYzTk

Trump incited a violent insurrection against our own government. Congress should be prepared to impeach & remove the President if the Vice President and Cabinet fail to adhere to their constitutional duty. We must protect our national security.

Donald Trump has shown he is a direct threat to the safety and security of Americans and the integrity of our democracy. The Vice President & Cabinet should immediately invoke the 25th Amendment to remove the President from office.

Neither the President, nor the members of Congress, nor the violent mobs who want to overturn the results of this election will succeed. 

They will fail. 

Our democracy will not. 

We Shall Overcome.

And Donald Trump is being aided and abetted by a group of Republican House and Senate members.

This is on them, as well.

We must rise from this nadir of shame. We must repair our democracy. We must heal our nation.

On August 24, 1814, the British stormed our Capitol and set fire to it.

Now the Capitol has again been breached and sieged.

Donald Trump incited this. He is responsible for this. And he is silent as this tragic moment continues.

Today I was sworn in for my second full term as a member of the United States Senate.

I’m honored to represent the people of New Jersey as we continue the fight for justice and more opportunity for all. 

I have so much hope for what we can accomplish together in this Congress.

The darkness of 2020 will be no match for the light of 2021. 

May this upcoming year shine bright with joy, love, and hope.

I wish you a very happy and healthy new year.

On January 6, Congress will fulfill its constitutional obligation and certify the results of the 2020 presidential election.

The American people made their decision. @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris won. Next week Congress will make it official.
